<h2 id="overview" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">What is Pimsleur?</h2>
<p class="mb-4">Pimsleur is an audio-based language learning program founded by Dr. Paul Pimsleur in 1963. The method focuses on building speaking skills through graduated interval recall — hearing and responding to words and phrases in context.</p>
<p class="mb-4">Unlike app-based learning with games and visuals, Pimsleur is primarily audio. Each lesson is 30 minutes of natural conversation practice with native speakers. You listen, respond, and build fluency through repetition and context.</p>
<p class="mb-4">The method is particularly effective for auditory learners and those who want to improve pronunciation and speaking speed. It's popular among business professionals preparing for international travel or relocation.</p>
