<h2 id="features" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Key Features</h2>
<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">1. Audio-First Methodology</h3>
<p class="mb-4">Each lesson is 30 minutes of audio-only learning. You hear a native speaker, then respond in the pause provided. This builds natural speaking reflexes without reading or writing.</p>
<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">2. Graduated Interval Recall</h3>
<p class="mb-4">The spaced repetition system replays new vocabulary at increasing intervals, helping you remember words naturally over time.</p>
<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">3. Core Conversation Skills</h3>
<p class="mb-4">Lessons focus on practical, real-world conversations. By the end of Level 1, you'll have basic survival conversations for travel and daily life.</p>
<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">4. Perfect English Pronunciation</h3>
<p class="mb-4">Premium Plus includes the "Voice Recognition — Perfect English" feature that compares your speech to native speakers and helps eliminate accent issues.</p>
<h3 class="text-xl font-semibold mt-6 mb-3">5. Reading Lessons</h3>
<p class="mb-4">Premium plans include reading lessons that teach you to read and write the language using phonetic principles.</p>
<h2 id="pros-cons" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Pros & Cons</h2>
<div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
<div class="bg-green-50 border border-green-200 rounded-xl p-6">
<h3 class="font-bold text-green-800 mb-3">✅ Pros</h3>
