<h2 id="verdict" class="text-2xl font-bold mt-8 mb-4">Our Verdict</h2>
<p class="mb-4"><strong>Pimsleur is unmatched for audio-based speaking practice.</strong> If you commute, exercise, or do housework and want to use that time for learning English, Pimsleur is the best option.</p>
<p class="mb-4">However, at $19.95+/month for audio-only content, it's expensive compared to comprehensive apps. It's best used as a supplement to app-based learning or as your primary audio resource.</p>
<p class="mb-4">Pimsleur is best for:</p>
<ul class="list-disc pl-6 mb-4 space-y-2">
<li>Commuters who want productive drive time</li>
<li>Auditory learners who prefer listening</li>
<li>Business professionals preparing for travel</li>
<li>Those focusing on pronunciation</li>
</ul>
